cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper proposes a deep learning method for optic disc and cup segmentation in fundus images, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) and a dice loss function, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper deals with medical images, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
